OL,3,CQueen grants Manx capital city status
OL,4,Cas she steps up for King
OL,6,FShe went on to sign the Letter Patent,
OL,7,Fa legal document signed by a monarch,
OL,8,Fto grant city status to Douglas.
OL,10,FThis particular Letter Patent is
OL,11,Fsignificant as it is the only one in
OL,12,Fexistence that has both Queen
OL,13,FElizabeth's and King Charles'
OL,14,Fsignature.
OL,16,Fwent on to read a speech on behalf of
OL,17,Fthe King, saying he was "so sorry" he
OL,18,Fcould not be there himself to
OL,19,Fcelebrate the "extremely special
OL,20,Foccasion".
